# Build the herdr lifecycle bridge into the spool

## Question

Add `herdr-plugin.toml` to herdr-pings with `[[events]]` hooks on `pane.closed` and `pane.exited` (evaluate `pane.agent_status_changed` — include only if its payload adds real signal) that append normalized records to the affected pane's existing spool file, per the locked contract (required `event`/`pane_id`/`timestamp`; extra fields allowed):

```json
{"event":"pane_exited","pane_id":"wF:p5","timestamp":"...","exit_code":1,"agent":"pi"}
{"event":"pane_closed","pane_id":"wF:p5","timestamp":"..."}
```

Distinct event names — NEVER `turn_ended`/`turn_error` from host events. Hook command reads `HERDR_PLUGIN_EVENT_JSON` (callsign precedent: `~/Code/joelhooks/herdr-callsign/sync-title.js`). Resolve what `pane.exited` vs `pane.closed` payloads actually distinguish (crash vs deliberate close) and record it. Dev via `herdr plugin link ~/Code/joelhooks/herdr-pings`.

Smoke: link the plugin, open a pane, `kill -9` its shell → a `pane_exited` record lands in that pane's spool and `herdr-ping-wait` delivers it.

Resolution: manifest + hook source, the exited/closed semantics receipt, smoke transcript.
